LOOPS-->

i in 0..n //(inclusive end)

i in 0 until n //(exclusive end)

i in 0..4 step 2 // STEP MUST BE POSITIVE

i in 10 downTo 1 step 2 // only way from high to low value

vec.forEach{
//use it as iterator
}

for (element in array) {
    println(element)
}

var i = 1
while (i <= 5) {
    println(i)
    i++ // Increment to avoid infinite loop
}


***
numbers.forEachIndexed { index, value -> 
        println("Index: $index, Value: $value")
}
OR
Use grid.indices for iterating through the row indices.
for (rowIndex in grid.indices) {
        for (colIndex in grid[rowIndex].indices) {
            val value = grid[rowIndex][colIndex]
            println("Element at [$rowIndex][$colIndex]: $value")
        }
}
